"v. 驱逐出国；脱离国籍 同根词：patriotism( n. 爱国主义)；patricid e(n. 杀父) v. (强迫)驱逐出国 = banish = exile; (自动)放弃国籍, 移居国外 【记】ex出, patri父亲, 国家－走出国家－(强迫 = 自动)出国 【参】patriotism(n 爱国心; 爱国精神); patricide(n 杀父) 【记】ex 出 + patri 父亲,国家 【相关】compatriot 同胞，同国人，eupatrid 世袭贵族，expatriate 驱逐国外，patriarch 家长，最年长者，patrimony (patri + money 父亲的钱)祖传财物，patriot 爱国者，patron 赞助人，资助人 expatriate (v.)  1768, from French expatrier ""banish"" (14c.), from ex- ""out of"" (see ex-) + patrie ""native land,"" from Latin patria ""one's native country,"" from pater (genitive patris) ""father"" (see father (n.); also compare patriot). Related: Expatriated; expatriating. The noun is from 1818, ""one who has been banished;"" main modern sense of ""one who chooses to live abroad"" is 1902."
